3.  **Locate words/phrases:** With your eyes closed or the book covered, try to recall specific words or phrases. You can even try to remember where they were on the page (e.g., at the top, bottom, left, right, or middle).
4.  **Practice on your own:** You can train yourself by reading a paragraph, taking a mental photograph, then covering the page and trying to locate (ଖୋଜିବା) important words by pointing to where they would be with your index finger.

This systematic use of VMDT helps to develop your visual memory, making it easier to remember what you have read.

